<br>
As a youngster, she was drawn to the ways of Karana by her father, and sought training with Te'Anara in Surefall Glade.  <br>
<br>
In her 10th season as a druid of Karana, the undead invaded Qeynos Hills, and in battle Sarhea fell, but rather than returning right back to Qeynos, she awoke in a place of mists and thunder, and heard the voice of Karana, who basically told her(the story is on my board) that she was better suited to be a fighter for the Rain, and when she awoke, once again in Surefall, Te'Anara told her that Hager Sureshot would teach her henceforth. <br>
<br>
 During this time, her teenage years, her father decided to tell her a little about her mother...well two things. One, that she was teir'dal. and two, that he'd loved the woman.<br>
<br>
<br>
So, she followed Karana as a ranger, she became attached to a druid.  <br>
<br>
When he'd had a bounty put on his head for the slaying of dark elves guarding the Nektulos forest, she decided to go seek out the one who'd placed the bounty, in hopes of giving her druid vital information....however, she fell in love with that dark elf, instead(damn the little blue skin guys*grin*).<br>
<br>
And through a series of events, some of which being(and this is just her point of view, not necessarily what actually happened) those she called her family spweing more raw hatred than she'd ever seen, then turning their backs on her, and having the dark elf declare that he'd never loved her at all, that it was all just a trick, etc etc....she learned true, pure Hatred...and Karana took his magic from her.<br>
<br>
Bereft of her love, AND her magic, she sought out a human she'd spoken to a good deal(Morgrist Vanadil, just to give credit where credit is due), and spoke with him about her life choices. <br>
<br>
Even after hearing about what it would take, she chose to walk the path of Hate, and went through a purification ritual. <br>
<br>
When she regained consciousness from the ordeal, she felt no magic within her, but instead, a pure, crystalline hatred...and then she was shown to the Dismal Rage, where she started training in the ways of sword dancing.<br>
<br>
<br>
And so on and so forth, to today, etc, yada yada.<br>
<br>
