Jiren was ambitious... to a fault. Picture the typical Shakespeare tragic hero, with one flaw that is his undoing. Such is Jiren and his ambition. <br>
Ambition led him to marry above his station. Wasn't enough though. Ambition then led him to be easily possessed by a demon created by the combined energies of Cazic-Thule and Innoruuk. The demon called itself the Scourgefist. The Scourgefist first had Jiren train as a monk to be its own personal weapon. It suppressed most of his personality and engaged in whatever mayhem pleased it. Jiren was angry with himself, captive in his own body. Power is what he wanted, but it was not he who had power, but instead the Scourgefist. He slipped his spirit into meditation through his monkly training, which kept the Scourgefist from destroying it completely. With the energy he conserved, he called to a Shamaness. The Shamaness faced off with the Scourgefist finally, and exorcised the demon.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, the realization hit Jiren too late. Without the Scourgefist, he was normal. He had no power. His years of monkly training were stripped from him. He was miserable, without skill, poor, pathetic. He began to loathe himself and the Shamaness for &quot;freeing&quot; him. His ambition again hurt him. Never before had his longing for power seemed this far-fetched. Hatred for all that happened engulfed him, and that hatred spread to all around him. Innoruuk enjoyed this immensely. Jiren and he came to an &quot;understanding&quot; of sorts. Jiren would make the world hate and fear him, as long as Innoruuk provided the means to do so.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=korzax>Korzax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/21/02 5:29:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2741.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Is dat joo?</span><hr size=1> Born in the mountains,<br>
